This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with the use of orthographic syllables as a basic unit for translation between related languages. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning models for translation, which could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of parallel corpora, which could place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of different basic units for translation, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
